  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0baf\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0baa\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Partners rejected Namal's idea",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to political sources, nine partner parties have rejected the idea put forward by Namal Rajapaksa, Member of Parliament of Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna, to change the government and form a new government together.",
        "Namal MP expressed this idea in a separate meeting with former minister and Member of Parliament Vasudeva Nanayakkara.",
        "It is reported that Vasudeva MP informed the party leaders of Namal's idea during a discussion with the leaders of the nine partner parties held at the Communist Party headquarters.",
        "All the party leaders have strongly rejected this issue and said that they cannot form a government together with the Rajapaksas as they are the cause of this crisis.",
        "Therefore, political sources say that the leaders of the partner parties have decided not to hold any discussion with Namal MP."
      ],
